post_text:
Tuesday, September 8th will be the first day of in-person learning. We will welcome our Traditional and Hybrid B students starting tomorrow. Virtual and Hybrid A students will sign on to the tech device by 8:30AM. Office hours are from 9:00AM - 2:00PM. All questions before or after these times should be directed to the homeroom teacher.

School hours for students are from 8:30AM - 2:30PM. All students and staff are required to wear a face mask.

Car riders - please go around back and wait in the car. Health checks will be conducted before entering the building.

All students will receive free breakfast and lunch until December 31, 2020.

Thank you.

Smaller class sizes are always a priority at Vineland Public Charter School! VPCS is a tuition-free Pre-Kindergarten through Eighth-grade school that offers class sizes that average about 15 students per class. In keeping with the New Jersey Social Distancing guidelines and the studentsâ€™ health and safety our priority, we currently have spots available for Grades K-8. We are in our planning phase for the upcoming school year and will be offering different types of learning environments to meet the needs of our students and families.

Parents and Guardians,

VPCS/BPCS/MPCS is offering a Summer Meal Program with pick up service at MPCS for the entire summer. The meals are on a first-come, first-serve basis for children 18 and under in the Cumberland County areas. In addition, if you have neighbors in need of meals, you are welcomed to pick up lunch for them as well. We will provide free meals every Monday and Wednesday from 11:30 AM -1:00 PM.

Thank you and we wish you a safe and enjoyable summer.

After consulting with the Cumberland County Department of Health/City of Vineland Health Department and while there are still no confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Cumberland County, we have made the decision to close our schools effective Tuesday, March 17, 2020.

Vineland Public Charter School will remain closed until after spring break, April 20th. We will continue to monitor this changing situation and consult with the Cumberland County Department of Health, County Department of Education and the Office of the Governor to determine if remote learning needs to be modified.

Please share!!

Please be advised of the following updated district information in regards to COVID-19:

School events are now limited to 250 occupants.

No out of state student trips are permitted.

Vineland Public Charter School will remain open unless otherwise recommended by the health department.

Currently our teachers are preparing for online learning for students to familiarize themselves with Google classroom. This will allow teachers to reach and instruct students in the event of a school closure. Information and resources will be sent home on Monday.

PLEASE REMEMBER: This information is subject to change at any time. We will share new information as we receive it.

They all had a great time!

post_text: Kindergarten had an awesome time exploring at the Discovery Museum. We became scientists who experimented with wind and gravity. We cooked and served food in a diner, learned about dinosaurs, played hockey and basketball, and pretended to be veterinarians, doctors and construction workers!

post_text: Kindergarten celebrated learning about community and the roles of a citizen with a job fair! Students created posters of what they want to be when they grow up and presented their future jobs to the class. KA is full of future teachers, doctors, veterinarians, sports players, ballerinas, and chefs.

post_text: Kindergarten welcomed a local artist George Perez to visit our school and teach us about his profession. The classes were able to watch as he showed us some of the skills he has learned in his 45 years as an artist. We watched as he illustrated cartoons and even made cartoon versions of some of the students!
